description: Do not use #[allow(dead_code)] or similar suppressions
alwaysApply: true
---

# No allow(dead_code)

**Do not use `#[allow(dead_code)]` (or `#[allow(dead_code)]` on fields/items) in this project.**

If the compiler reports dead code:

- **Use the value** somewhere (e.g. in logs, tests, or logic), or
- **Remove the code** if it is truly unused, or
- **Prefix with `_`** only when required by an API/schema and cannot be removed.

Do not suppress the warning with `#[allow(dead_code)]`.
